IN THE 40S, LIBRARY CUSTODIANS LIVED IN THE LIBRARIES WITH THEIR FAMILIES.
RONALD CLARK THOUGHT HE WAS WAS RICH UNTIL HI DAD TOLD HIM THEY WERE POOR.
HIS DAD TOOK PRIDE IN HIS WORK AND EVEN WAXED THE TOP OF THE SHELVES
WHEN HE WANTED TO KNOW SOMETHING, HE GOT UP IN THE MIDDLE OF THE NIGHT AND LOOKED IT UP
HE WANTED TO BE A NORMAL KID WITH A HOUSE BUT HE LEARNED TO LOVE LIVING IN THE LIBRARY BECAUSE HE HAD THE MOST BOOKS
HE WAS THE FIRST TO GRADUATE IN HIS FAMILY
HE BECAME A PROFESSOR WITH HIS NAME ON THE DOOR
HE SHOWED HIS DAD AND HIS DAD JUST NODDED'
IT WAS ALL POSSIBLE BECAUSE OF THE LIBRARY
RONALD'S DAD WAS A CUSTODIAN IN THE LIBRARY IN THE 40S
HIS WHOLE FAMILY LIVED IN THE LIBRARY
HIS DAD WAXED THE TOPS THE BOOKCASE
HIS FRIENDS NEVER CAME OVER BECAUSE HE WAS ASHAMED
WHEN HE WAS LITTLE, HE WENT DOWN IN THE LIBRARY AND PICKED OUT BOOKS AND LEARNED EVERYTHING HE COULD
HE WANTED TO BE NORMAL AT THE TIME BUT HE'S GLAD HE LIVED IN THE LIBRRAY
NONE OF THE REST OF HIS FAMILY GRADUATED HIGH SCHOOL
HIS DAD WAS QUIET WHEN HE SHOWED HIM HIS DOOR
